24 SECTION 2. REAPPROPRIATION AUTHORITY -- LIBRARY PROJECTS. There is
25 hereby reappropriated to the Idaho Commission for Libraries any unexpended
26 and unencumbered balance appropriated or reappropriated to the Idaho Com-
27 mission for Libraries from the ARPA Capital Projects Fund for fiscal year
28 2025, to be used for nonrecurring expenditures related to library capital
29 projects for the period July 1, 2025, through June 30, 2026. The Office
30 of the State Controller shall confirm the reappropriation amount by fund,
31 expense class, and program, with the Budget and Policy Analysis Division
32 of the Legislative Services Office prior to processing the reappropriation
33 authorized herein.
34 SECTION 3. USE OF APPROPRIATED FUNDS. State-appropriated funds shall
35 not be utilized to support diversity, equity, inclusion, or social justice
36 ideology as part of any activities, clubs, events, or organizations. Each
37 library that receives state-appropriated funds shall submit a written re-
38 port of its expenditures related to these activities to the Joint Finance-

