3 SECTION 4. PROVIDING FOR A REPORT ON STATUTORY ADHERENCE. The Idaho
4 Commission for Libraries shall designate an existing employee to confirm by
5 means of affidavit that state libraries adhere to Section 18-1517B, Idaho
6 Code. The designated employee shall also coordinate with the Department
7 of Education to confirm by means of affidavit that schools libraries ad-
8 here to Sections 18-1517B and 33-137, Idaho Code. The Idaho Commission for
9 Libraries shall provide a report to the Joint Finance-Appropriations Com-
10 mittee no later than December 1, 2025, including the commission's findings.
11 The report and information contained therein shall be determined by the Bud-
12 get and Policy Analysis Division of the Legislative Services Office.
13 SECTION 5. FEDERAL FUNDING RESTRICTIONS. Pursuant to Section
14 67-3511(2), Idaho Code, legislative appropriations shall not be transferred
15 from one fund to another fund unless expressly approved by the Legislature.
16 Appropriations made pursuant to this act contingent on anticipated federal
17 funding, grants, or programs shall not be supplanted by state funds in the
18 event of any reduction or elimination of such federal support without leg-
19 islative approval. The agency receiving the appropriation shall take all
20 necessary actions to ensure that the state is not obligated to replace lost
21 federal funds. Pursuant to Section 67-1917, Idaho Code, the agency will
22 submit an inventory of federal funds utilized by the agency. State funds ap-
23 propriated to satisfy match requirements for federal funds shall be reverted
24 to the maximum extent possible if federal funds requiring match are reduced
25 or eliminated. The agency shall promptly notify the Budget and Policy Anal-
26 ysis Division of the Legislative Services Office of any significant changes
27 to related federal funding, grants, or programs.
28 SECTION 6. CONDITIONS, LIMITATIONS, AND RESTRICTIONS. Appropriations
29 made pursuant to this act are subject to the conditions, limitations, and re-
30 strictions specified in this act.
31 SECTION 7. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
